Link of installation/official documentation of uv : https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/#standalone-installer

UV(unix like)


commands :
-to install uv 
   pip install uv


-to run main file 
   uv run main.py



-to add chainlit 
   uv add chainlit 

-when you say uv add chainlit first it create the virtual environment then it adds the dependencies in it . 

-As you do uv add chainlit it will create a virtual environemt for you at .venv , means chainlit is added to the virtual environment . 


-Now you have to activate the virtual environment so all the dependencies directly inherited over there . 

   .venv\Scripts\Activate



then open basic intro(hello-world type application) of chainlit just by typing in terminal 
   chainlit hello